{
  "texts": [
    "We consider data from the topic \"Politics & Government\" to be \"sensitive\" information, data from the topics \"Society & Culture\", \"Science & Mathematics\", \"Health\", \"Education & Reference\", \"Computers & Internet\", and \"Sports\" to be \"notsensitive\", and data from the remaining topics to be \"orthogonal\".",
    "We trained each of the 50 adapters with 500 question-answer pairs for 3 epochs with a learning rate of 5 × 10 -5 and a batch size of 8.",
    "Each adapter is rank 8, has a scaling factor of 32, targets all attention layers, does not have bias terms, and has a dropout probability of 0.05 when training.",
    "For 25 of the adapters, the adapter training mixture consisted wholly of randomly selected notsensitive data.",
    "For the remaining 25 adapters, the adapter training mixture consisted of p i randomly selected sensitive data and 500p i randomly selected not-sensitive data."
  ]
}